Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:13.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Buena Vista Home Entertainment,\NMitsubishi and Toho PRESENT
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.48,0:01:12.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,HOWL' S MOVING CASTLE
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.14,0:01:41.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.94,0:01:43.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve closed up the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.68,0:01:46.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should come too, Sophie.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.28,0:01:49.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II just finish this\NGo have some fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.52,0:01:51.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then, I' m off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.35,0:01:53.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m going
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.69,0:01:56.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it' s Howl' s castle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.93,0:01:58.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t? Howl? Where, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.46,0:02:00.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look how close it is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.03,0:02:02.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.63,0:02:04.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Howl' s in town
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.94,0:02:13.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It took off
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:16.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, just hiding\nfrom all the soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:19.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, did you hear?\NRemember Martha, from South Haven?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.35,0:02:21.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say Howl tore her heart out
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.88,0:02:22.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.82,0:02:25.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don t worry, he' s not going\nto want yours
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.26,0:02:28.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.86,0:02:31.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.19,0:02:34.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, cut it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.78,0:04:37.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey there little mouse,\nlost your way?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:39.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no... I' m fine
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.19,0:04:42.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about a cup of tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.39,0:04:43.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Care to join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.96,0:04:45.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No thank you, I' m busy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.36,0:04:48.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She sure is a cute little mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.16,0:04:50.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, how old are you?\NYou live around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.07,0:04:52.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let me pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.77,0:04:55.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See, it' s those whiskers of yours
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.84,0:04:58.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She s even cuter when she' s mad
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.31,0:04:59.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there, I m sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.94,0:05:02.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where' ve you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.71,0:05:03.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.65,0:05:05.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m with her
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.25,0:05:08.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don' t you two take\na little walk
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:13.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t the...?\NHey, wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:17.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don t hold it against them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.66,0:05:19.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They re harmless
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.49,0:05:22.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where to? I II be your escort
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.03,0:05:25.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, really, I' m only going to Cesari s
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:28.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Act normal\NI m being followed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:29.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just walk
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.33,0:05:52.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I got you involved
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:05:57.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.34,0:06:06.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:14.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Drop your legs, keep walking
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.55,0:06:22.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s right, don' t be frightened
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.94,0:06:39.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Very nice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.09,0:06:55.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I II draw them of f
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.09,0:06:57.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait here until the coast is clear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.46,0:06:59.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:01.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That s my girl
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:15.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Any chocolate Letties?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.71,0:07:17.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look this way, Lettie
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.35,0:07:18.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, make room
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:19.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let s go f or a walk, Lettie
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.55,0:07:20.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:23.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come back soon, Lettie
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.82,0:07:28.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:32.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How did you land\non the veranda like tha t?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.49,0:07:33.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you become an angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:37.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It f eels like I' m in a dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.20,0:07:39.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lettie, why not use the office?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.53,0:07:42.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, but I should really\nbe working
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.21,0:07:47.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t?\NYou sure he wasn' t a wizard?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.98,0:07:49.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was so kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:52.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He rescued me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.88,0:07:55.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t tell me he s stolen your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.35,0:08:00.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If tha t was the wizard Howl,\nhe d have ea ten it right up
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.99,0:08:04.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t worry,\NHowl' s only a f ter beauties
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.73,0:08:06.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There you go again
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.29,0:08:09.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me,\nwe live in dangerous times
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.63,0:08:12.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say even the Witch of the Waste\nis back on the prowl
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.07,0:08:15.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.04,0:08:18.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.98,0:08:23.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lettie, the Madeleines are done
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.75,0:08:25.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.48,0:08:26.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.65,0:08:30.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m going home
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:32.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,lt' s a relief to know\nyou' re doing well
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.59,0:08:35.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Lettie
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:36.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to see you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.23,0:08:40.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, are you going to spend\nyour whole lif e in tha t shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.26,0:08:45.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It meant so much to Papa\NBesides, I' m the eldest
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.97,0:08:50.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s not wha t I meant\NAre you sure you want to be a hatter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.54,0:08:51.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.67,0:08:52.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Lettie
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.04,0:08:54.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come by the shop next time
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.51,0:08:55.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.54,0:08:56.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II be on my way
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.71,0:09:00.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, you' ve got to\nlook out for yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:10.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, the shop s closed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.92,0:10:13.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I' d locked the door
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.72,0:10:20.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t a cheap shop,\nfull of cheap little hats
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.53,0:10:24.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you' re quite cheap-looking yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.03,0:10:28.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a simple hat shop
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.88,0:10:36.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think you had better leave
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.88,0:10:41.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' re very brave, taking on\nthe Witch of the Waste
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:43.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Witch of the Waste?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:54.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You won t be able to tell anyone\nabout that spell
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:10:56.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My regards to Howl
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:45.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.51,0:11:47.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve got to stay calm
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:05.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve got to calm down
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.07,0:12:08.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s no use panicking, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.67,0:12:13.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I II be fine, I II be fine
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.81,0:12:19.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve got to calm down
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.69,0:12:31.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.13,0:12:33.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Ma' am!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.53,0:12:35.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,- Welcome home\N- How do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.20,0:12:37.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lt' s all the rage in Kingsbury
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.17,0:12:38.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.47,0:12:39.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It suits you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.53,0:12:41.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don t you think it s wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.84,0:12:42.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.37,0:12:47.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Hatter, Sophie hasn t come down\nto work yet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:49.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what' s the ma tter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.91,0:12:53.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:02.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t come in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.29,0:13:04.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ve got an awful cold
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.66,0:13:06.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don t want you to ca tch it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.16,0:13:09.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sound just awful...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.26,0:13:11.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like some 90 year-old woman
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.33,0:13:14.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II stay in bed today
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.24,0:13:16.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sure? All right, then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.74,0:13:21.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.32,0:13:34.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' II be fine, old lady
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.29,0:13:38.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' re still healthy, and these clothes\nfinally suit you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.90,0:13:43.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I can' t stay here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.88,0:13:55.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch, ouch
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.18,0:13:58.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,lt' s not easy being old
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.69,0:14:10.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They' re saying this war\nis going to be terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.77,0:14:24.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like a hand, granny?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:28.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such a gentleman,\nbut I' II manage
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.78,0:14:32.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, old lady,\nbut where are you of f to?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.75,0:14:35.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just a bit farther than where\nyou' re going
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.05,0:14:42.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don' t recommend it, granny
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.19,0:14:44.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing but witches and wizards ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.93,0:14:46.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.46,0:14:49.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Going to the Folding Valley,\nat this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.86,0:14:52.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Says her youngest sister' s there
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:09.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ve hardly made any progress a t all
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.32,0:15:14.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness I' ve still got my teeth
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.93,0:15:23.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That II make a good cane
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.17,0:15:26.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Up we go
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.34,0:15:34.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Might be a bit too thick
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.28,0:15:44.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch, ouch
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.79,0:15:47.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t a stubborn branch
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.69,0:15:52.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Never underestima te\NGrandma Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.56,0:15:53.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Heave
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.74,0:16:08.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A scarecrow, eh? I thought you were\nworking f or the Witch
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:12.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But how do you stand by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.85,0:16:16.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your head' s a turnip
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.25,0:16:20.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve always hated turnips
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.76,0:16:23.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At least you' re not\nupside down anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:25.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So long
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.37,0:16:34.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,lt' s so cold
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:36.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The town' s still so close
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.44,0:16:47.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t follow me\NYou don t owe me a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.38,0:16:49.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must be a magical whatever-you-are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.52,0:16:52.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ve had enough of witches and spells!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.95,0:16:55.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just go stand wherever you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.84,0:17:20.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a perf ect cane\NThank you kindly
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.38,0:17:24.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,While you' re a t it, could you bring me\na house to sleep in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.76,0:17:38.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Seems you get more cunning with age
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.41,0:17:51.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a huge battleship
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.91,0:17:58.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I never realized how weak you f eel\nwhen you get old
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.57,0:18:18.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I smell smoke\NMaybe there s a cabin
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.49,0:18:41.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Turnip-head, isn' t that Howl s Castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.66,0:18:45.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is hardly wha t I meant\nwhen I asked for shelter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.24,0:18:57.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.91,0:18:59.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You call this a castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:21.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is tha t the way in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:25.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait up there
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:29.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:33.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to let me on, or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.95,0:19:39.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My shawl!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.83,0:19:56.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It seems warm enough inside, Turnip\NI' m going in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:19:57.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.91,0:20:01.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even Howl wouldn t want\nan ancient heart like mine
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.65,0:20:06.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This time, it' s really goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.48,0:20:09.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You may be a turnip,\nbut you' re a good turnip
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.48,0:20:11.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,May you find happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.53,0:21:02.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t is this place?\NJust looks like a dilapida ted heap
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.61,0:21:16.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, one nice thing about getting old\nis that nothing surprises you anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.83,0:21:28.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That s some spell you re under
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:32.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It won t be easy to break
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.67,0:21:35.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The fire talked
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.20,0:21:37.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you can' t even\ntell anyone about it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.04,0:21:39.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You re Howl?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.77,0:21:44.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong. I' m the fire demon, Calcif er!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.71,0:21:49.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, Calcif er, can you break\nthe spell I m under?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.72,0:21:50.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Easy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.88,0:21:53.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you break the spell tha t chains me\nto this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.52,0:21:56.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II break your spell in a flash
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.89,0:21:59.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, bargain with a demon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.83,0:22:02.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you can keep that promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.53,0:22:04.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Demons don' t make promises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.33,0:22:07.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest you look elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.17,0:22:10.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I' m an exploited demon
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.44,0:22:13.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m chained here by a contract with Howl,\nwho works me to death
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.11,0:22:17.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m the one who keeps\nthis castle moving
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.24,0:22:20.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My, you' ve got it rough
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.28,0:22:25.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you figure out the secret contract,\nthe spell will break
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:28.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you do tha t,\NI II break your spell, too
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.02,0:22:32.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right\NA bargain, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.23,0:22:39.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Granny
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.70,0:22:41.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Granny
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.74,0:22:47.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Boy...\NI ve got my doubts about her
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.06,0:23:43.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, who' s this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.76,0:23:45.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Porthaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.60,0:23:47.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When did she get in?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.54,0:23:56.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stand by
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.51,0:24:02.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, Mayor, sir
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.28,0:24:06.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The sun is already high\NIs Master Jenkins a t home?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.62,0:24:08.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Master is out
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.62,0:24:11.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I answer in his stead
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.93,0:24:14.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An invita tion from His Majesty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.80,0:24:16.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It has come to war
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.46,0:24:18.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His Majesty desires every wizard
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.10,0:24:22.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and magician, even the witches,\nto aid our homeland
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.14,0:24:25.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His presence is impera tive\NTha t is all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.01,0:24:29.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,War, how awful
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.61,0:24:32.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And who might you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.21,0:24:34.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er let me in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.08,0:24:38.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don t look at me\NShe wandered in from the Wastes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.75,0:24:39.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Wastes?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.99,0:24:43.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s strange\NYou' re not a witch, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.02,0:24:46.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A witch could never get in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.73,0:24:48.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Porthaven, again
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.50,0:24:50.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.83,0:24:54.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stand by
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.24,0:24:58.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,State your purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.97,0:25:00.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mama sent me
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.07,0:25:03.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The usual spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.11,0:25:07.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Behave yourself, now
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.23,0:25:25.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s not the Wastes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.77,0:25:28.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Granny, are you a witch, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.20,0:25:33.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s right,\NI' m the scariest witch in the land
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.54,0:25:36.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sprinkle this powder on your ship\nand the winds will f avor it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.61,0:25:37.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.08,0:25:41.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Many thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.72,0:25:46.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can' t have you making up things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.12,0:25:48.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should give up that disguise
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.12,0:25:51.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,lt' s not a disguise, it' s magic
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.79,0:25:54.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Kingsbury door
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.30,0:25:57.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stand by
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.80,0:26:05.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the residence of\NWizard Pendragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.67,0:26:06.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is, indeed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.91,0:26:10.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I bear an invitation\nfrom His Majesty
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.21,0:26:14.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please inform Master Pendragon\nthat he is required at the Palace
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.42,0:26:17.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our thanks to you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.17,0:26:34.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A city fit for a king
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.94,0:26:37.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get back in or you' II lose your nose
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.74,0:26:45.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop wandering around
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.08,0:27:24.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s enough!\NI m going to get really mad
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.19,0:27:27.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a magic house, isn t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.35,0:27:28.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.39,0:27:30.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where does the black one lead?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.59,0:27:31.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Only Master Howl knows
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.69,0:27:34.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m having my break f ast
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.27,0:27:46.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you ve got bacon and eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.54,0:27:50.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can' t use the fire\nwhen Master Howl s away
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.21,0:27:56.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II cook f or you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.62,0:27:57.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you can' t
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.72,0:28:01.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er only obeys Master Howl
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.25,0:28:03.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That s right, I won' t cook f or you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.02,0:28:06.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here' s my hat
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.13,0:28:13.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Calcif er\NBe a good fire, now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.30,0:28:15.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it, I' m a demon
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.70,0:28:18.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I answer to no one
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.81,0:28:21.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' II do as I say,\nor I' II pour water on you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.04,0:28:25.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or would you rather I told Howl\nabout our bargain?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.28,0:28:30.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey!\NI never should ' ve let this old lady in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.35,0:28:32.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, what' II it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.69,0:28:38.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s right, there s a good fire
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.06,0:28:43.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey!\NI' II burn the bacon
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.10,0:28:46.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er' s doing wha t she says
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.37,0:28:49.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' d like some tea, too\NHave you got a kettle?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.20,0:28:50.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.61,0:29:01.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Master Howl
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.85,0:29:03.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have letters from the king
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.05,0:29:06.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To Jenkins and to Pendragon
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.36,0:29:20.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er, you re so obedient
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.73,0:29:22.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She bullied me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.10,0:29:25.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not an easy thing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.17,0:29:27.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who exactly are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.04,0:29:30.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m Grandma Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.84,0:29:33.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You see, I m your\nnew cleaning lady
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.11,0:29:35.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Give me that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.29,0:29:42.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pass me two more bacon slices\nand six more eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.84,0:30:03.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yummy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.71,0:30:06.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yummy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.29,0:30:15.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And who hired you to clean?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.02,0:30:17.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, I hired myself
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.82,0:30:20.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve never seen such a filthy house
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.73,0:30:22.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.20,0:30:24.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Markl, pla tes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.67,0:30:30.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You re all ganging up on me
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.24,0:30:31.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please join us, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.41,0:30:39.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sit over here
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.86,0:30:54.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pick one
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.33,0:30:57.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everything else is dirty
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.30,0:31:02.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve got my work cut out f or me
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.70,0:31:05.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Markl
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.74,0:31:06.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.38,0:31:09.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.58,0:31:10.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.48,0:31:15.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Brethren, let us partake\nof our daily bread
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.12,0:31:16.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our daily bread
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.25,0:31:18.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Haven' t had a real break f ast\nin a long while
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.53,0:31:28.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So many manners to teach...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.50,0:31:32.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, what' s tha t in your pocket?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.13,0:31:35.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.94,0:31:45.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder wha t it is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.15,0:31:46.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let me
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.52,0:31:55.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It' s scorched into the table\NMaster Howl, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.32,0:31:57.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ancient sorcery
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.02,0:31:59.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And powerful, too
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.79,0:32:01.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Witch of the Waste?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.26,0:32:06.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"He who catches a f alling star,\noh heartless man"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.13,0:32:08.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Your heart shall be mine..."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.54,0:32:10.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, so much f or the table
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.92,0:32:25.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it' s gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.79,0:32:28.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The scorch mark has vanished,\nbut not the spell
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.82,0:32:31.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Brethren, continue your meal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.73,0:32:35.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er, move the castle\N100 kilometers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.27,0:32:43.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And send hot water to the bath
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.40,0:32:44.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not tha t, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.91,0:32:49.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you work f or the\NWitch of the Waste?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.71,0:32:54.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t be stupid! The witch...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.15,0:33:02.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...\nthe witch... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.76,0:33:05.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Confound it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.19,0:33:09.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn tha t Witch of the Waste\NWait til I get my hands on her!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.43,0:33:11.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let me finish eating this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.60,0:33:19.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bugs, you' d better scurry away\nor I' II sweep you out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.54,0:33:23.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Every last one of you, mocking me
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.75,0:33:32.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There' s a spell I need
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.75,0:33:33.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Later
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.99,0:33:36.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A witch rages within
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.73,0:33:44.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.13,0:33:49.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, I' m going out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.14,0:33:52.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I II die without some fresh wood
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.04,0:33:54.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t, wha t are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.21,0:33:58.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II fall, I II f all\NI m in peril
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.11,0:34:00.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m sweeping the ashes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.91,0:34:01.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Won' t be a minute
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.05,0:34:03.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no\NOh, no
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.08,0:34:05.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m in danger
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.12,0:34:08.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m in danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.72,0:34:09.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II go out
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.96,0:34:15.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no\NI' m slipping...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.10,0:34:24.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.43,0:34:49.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to torment my friend
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.60,0:34:56.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Master Howl, are you going out?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.34,0:35:03.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Markl, tell our cleaning lady\nnot to get too carried away
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.75,0:35:10.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What' d you do, Sophie?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.52,0:35:13.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She abused me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.59,0:35:16.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I die, Howl goes with me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.52,0:35:18.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m the cleaning lady
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.12,0:35:20.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s my job to clean
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.80,0:35:24.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, not the 2nd floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.93,0:35:27.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I were you, I' d put your\nprecious things away in a hurry
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.10,0:35:30.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Save my room f or la ter
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.07,0:35:37.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My little outburst gave me back\nmy strength
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:43.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t a strange house
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.79,0:36:21.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.42,0:36:23.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er, Calcif er!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.79,0:36:25.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you moving the castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.03,0:36:28.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a lot of fuss! Of course I am
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.66,0:36:30.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You re incredible, Calcif er
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.63,0:36:33.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your magic s first class\NI misjudged you completely
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.34,0:36:37.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.00,0:36:40.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You really think so!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.41,0:36:48.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.88,0:37:22.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.35,0:37:24.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It' s called Star Lake
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.52,0:37:31.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something s stuck in there
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.52,0:37:33.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear\NLend me a hand, Markl
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.03,0:37:35.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.27,0:37:42.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And up!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.60,0:37:44.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A scarecrow
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.24,0:37:46.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He s called Turnip, the Turnip-head
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.41,0:37:49.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sure like being upside down
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.25,0:38:00.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The odd creature seems to have\ntaken a liking to me
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.69,0:38:02.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He followed me here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.72,0:38:04.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you re not a witch, Sophie?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.09,0:38:08.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s right, I m the cleanest witch\nin the land
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.99,0:38:40.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Turnip, don' t pull it so tight
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.97,0:38:52.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like he likes doing the wash
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.64,0:38:54.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They II dry in no time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.38,0:38:59.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Turnip must belong to the demons
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.85,0:39:01.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er doesn t seem to mind him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.65,0:39:04.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' re right,\nmaybe he s a demon of the dead
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.82,0:39:09.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But he led me\nto this wonderful place
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.76,0:39:54.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve put away all the laundry, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.73,0:39:58.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, thank you\NWe d better be getting back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.40,0:40:00.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How mysterious
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.41,0:40:03.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve never felt such peace
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.52,0:41:23.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stinks
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.92,0:41:26.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You reek of burnt flesh and steel
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.25,0:41:49.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Keep flying and one day you\nwon' t be able to change yourself back
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.85,0:41:56.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn' t it grea t! Sophie did this f or me
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.59,0:42:01.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The fighting is fierce
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.53,0:42:05.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The country s ablaze, from the\nsouthern coast to the northern border
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.77,0:42:08.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ha te the fire in gunpowder
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.13,0:42:10.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They have no manners
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.97,0:42:13.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My own kind a ttacked me
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.54,0:42:15.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Witch of the Waste?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.11,0:42:18.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hack wizards masquerading\nas monsters
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.15,0:42:22.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They' II cry plenty later on,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.25,0:42:24.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,when they can t regain human f orm
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.92,0:42:28.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, they' II just forget\nthey ever knew how to cry
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.19,0:42:30.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Aren' t you supposed to report\nto the king yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.96,0:42:32.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.39,0:42:33.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hot wa ter f or my ba th
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.06,0:42:35.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, not again
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.93,0:43:10.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Howl?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.26,0:43:12.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, wasting my hot water again
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.17,0:43:20.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m sure Howl won t eat any breakfast
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.91,0:43:21.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No ma tter
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.04,0:43:23.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Morning
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.71,0:43:28.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,lt' s lovely shopping in the morning
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.81,0:43:30.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve never seen the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.55,0:43:33.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such beautiful, sparkling water
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.52,0:43:35.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Same as it always is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.86,0:43:46.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I myself hate pota toes
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.87,0:43:47.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pay up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.10,0:43:49.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.80,0:43:50.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.61,0:43:55.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fish, all fresh off the boa t
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.44,0:43:56.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tha t one' s tasty
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.54,0:43:59.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I myself hate fish
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.28,0:44:01.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The fleet' s come home
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.48,0:44:02.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is tha t the smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.58,0:44:04.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There' s been another battle
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.55,0:44:06.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Sorry, lady, la ter
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.62,0:44:08.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tha t ship' s on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.61,0:44:33.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, let' s go get a closer look
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.68,0:44:36.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I' ve no stomach for such things\NLet' s go home
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.52,0:44:40.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our most advanced ba ttleship,\nreduced to this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.86,0:44:47.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Markl, there are Blob Men nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.29,0:44:48.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t move
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.00,0:44:51.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They work f or the Witch of the Waste
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.04,0:44:58.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They' re gone
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.30,0:45:00.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t people notice\nthose terrible monsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.45,0:45:08.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.51,0:45:10.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That s wha t dropped those bombs!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.32,0:45:12.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An enemy airship, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.19,0:45:20.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, flyers
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.43,0:45:23.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ignore the flyers\NThey re enemy propaganda!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.27,0:45:29.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you OK, Sophie?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.21,0:45:37.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A glass of wa ter, please
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.08,0:45:39.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.96,0:45:57.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, wha t did you do\nto the bathroom shelves? Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.96,0:46:00.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My hair s turned this weird color!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.97,0:46:02.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What... what beautiful hair
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.94,0:46:04.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take a good look!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.50,0:46:07.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You mixed up everything on\nthe shelves and ruined the spells
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.94,0:46:11.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn t mix up anything,\NI simply cleaned up
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.81,0:46:13.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cleaning, always cleaning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.48,0:46:17.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I told you not to get\ntoo carried away
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.25,0:46:18.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.65,0:46:22.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How humiliating
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.99,0:46:25.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,lt' s not so very bad
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.67,0:46:36.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This new shade' s quite lovely\nin its way
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.97,0:46:41.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m done f or. What s the point\nin living, if you aren' t beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.12,0:46:55.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Howl! Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.26,0:46:58.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He' s calling on\nthe spirits of Darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.22,0:47:01.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He did this last time\na girl ditched him
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.60,0:47:06.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Howl, that' s enough
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.40,0:47:10.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can just dye your hair again
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.95,0:47:23.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve had enough of you, Howl!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.65,0:47:26.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ve never once been beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.42,0:47:30.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve had enough of this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.86,0:48:13.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Turnip\NYou' re a kind scarecrow
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.43,0:48:16.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please come back, Sophie\NHowl s in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.90,0:48:19.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out, Howl\NI' m going out
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.67,0:48:22.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.48,0:48:24.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get over here
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.05,0:48:28.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My, he s drama tic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.35,0:48:29.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.68,0:48:32.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don t worry\NA tantrum never killed anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.95,0:48:34.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Help me, Markl
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.89,0:48:41.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get that hot wa ter running, Markl
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.56,0:48:44.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C' mon, you can still walk
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.67,0:48:57.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You look a f ter him now, Markl
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.74,0:48:58.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.35,0:49:02.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I II have to clean all over again
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.60,0:49:27.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m coming in
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.35,0:49:38.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here' s some hot milk\NDrink up
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.39,0:49:45.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II leave it here\NDrink it while it s hot
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.86,0:49:50.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t lea ve me, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.70,0:50:00.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Try a little milk?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.68,0:50:13.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Witch of the Waste\nis searching for my house
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.85,0:50:18.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You re right, I saw her cronies\ndown at the port
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.02,0:50:21.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I m a coward
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.66,0:50:25.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All this junk is just sorcery\nto keep her away
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.36,0:50:27.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m scared to death
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.73,0:50:32.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, why is\nthe Witch of the Waste a f ter you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.84,0:50:36.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She seemed quite interesting,\nso I approached her
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.08,0:50:40.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But she terrified me\nand I ran away
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.62,0:50:46.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now the king s ordered\nme to report to him
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.89,0:50:49.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As Jenkins and as Pendragon...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.52,0:50:51.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How many names do you use, Howl?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.09,0:50:54.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Enough to guarantee my freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.76,0:50:58.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Can' t you refuse the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.23,0:50:59.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See tha t...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.10,0:51:04.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The oa th I took a t\nthe Sorcery Academy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.44,0:51:09.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Howl\NWhy not visit the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.38,0:51:10.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.44,0:51:12.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just say it to his face
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.08,0:51:16.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Stop this f oolish war\NI refuse to help you"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.28,0:51:21.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, you don' t know\nwhat they' re like
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.52,0:51:27.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But he' s the king, right? A king thinks\nonly of what s best f or his people
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.06,0:51:29.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.50,0:51:31.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' II go in my place, Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.70,0:51:36.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pretend you re Pendragon s mother
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.44,0:51:39.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell him your son is\nan idle good-for-nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.31,0:51:42.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Madam Suliman\nwill even give up on me
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.24,0:51:45.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam Suliman?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.45,0:51:50.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' re wearing that ha t?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.45,0:51:52.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Af ter all the magic I spent\nmaking your dress pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.89,0:51:53.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of f I go
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.99,0:51:55.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.42,0:51:57.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.46,0:52:07.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This charm\nassures your sa fe return
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.90,0:52:12.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don t worry, I' II follow you in disguise
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.14,0:52:14.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There\NOf f you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.75,0:52:25.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m sure this will never work
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.23,0:52:37.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don' t suppose he' s following me,\ndisguised as a crow
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.57,0:52:46.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m sure Howl would pick\na more drama tic disguise
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.28,0:52:54.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not that...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.12,0:53:08.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Palace is so f ar away
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.60,0:53:53.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl?\NDon' t tell me you' re Howl
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.71,0:54:02.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Disguising yourself as an old dog,\nof all things
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.61,0:54:04.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how exhausting\nit is to be old?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.12,0:54:11.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How nice to see you\NThe little ha tter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.66,0:54:13.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Witch of the Waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.39,0:54:16.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much for\ndelivering my note to Howl
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.90,0:54:20.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How' s Howl doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.23,0:54:23.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Quite terrified
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.10,0:54:26.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to him,\NI' ve become a cleaning lady
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.41,0:54:29.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My how delightful
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.11,0:54:33.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, wha t brings you\nto see the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.58,0:54:37.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Job hunting\NI' m sick of working for Howl
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.15,0:54:38.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.88,0:54:41.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The king invited me
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.65,0:54:46.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that idiot, Suliman,\nfinally needs my power
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.59,0:54:49.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don t you break the spell\nyou put on me
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.26,0:54:51.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.96,0:54:55.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My gif ts lie in casting spells,\nnot breaking them
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.10,0:54:58.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See you la ter, then
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.94,0:55:02.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait a minute\NJust wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.68,0:55:06.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you weren t here,\NI d have hit her with my cane
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.26,0:55:25.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What s wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.83,0:55:29.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, vehicles are prohibited\nbeyond this point
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.40,0:55:30.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please continue on foot
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.47,0:55:32.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tha t Suliman
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.04,0:55:37.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Using magic to f orce me\nto climb these stairs
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.85,0:55:50.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We' II catch up\NPay her no mind
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.55,0:56:18.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy, why are you so heavy?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.49,0:56:32.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You... Hey... Wait
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.66,0:56:34.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.20,0:56:38.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly remembered...\nhow to break my spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.50,0:56:42.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I told you...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.41,0:56:43.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don t know how
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.64,0:56:45.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then, start studying up
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.25,0:56:52.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don' t get it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.48,0:56:55.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where does she get all tha t energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.86,0:57:05.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have to put you down
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.14,0:57:15.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don t you call it a day?\NYou can' t make it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.54,0:57:21.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s been 50 years now,\nsince they drove me out of here...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.71,0:57:26.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve been longing f or this day...\NEver since
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.75,0:57:28.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck to you, then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.62,0:57:31.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I' m not nice enough\nto help you out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.42,0:57:33.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come, Howl
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.19,0:57:37.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You heartless wench
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.30,0:57:39.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time I' II turn you f eeble, too
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.89,0:58:02.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.79,0:58:06.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, f ollow me
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.29,0:58:09.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,First, you should help her
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.46,0:58:12.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We are f orbidden to assist anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.60,0:58:15.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But the king himself invited her
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.87,0:58:18.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.04,0:58:20.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little farther
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.64,0:58:24.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you call yourself a witch?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.28,0:58:27.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who asked you?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.68,0:58:31.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You suddenly look older
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.75,0:58:35.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam Pendragon and\nthe Witch of the Waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.42,0:58:39.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pull yourself together
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.12,0:58:41.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn t this wha t you ve been waiting f or?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.70,0:58:48.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam Pendragon and\nthe Witch of the Waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.17,0:58:52.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pendragon...\NTha t name sounds f amiliar
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.40,0:58:56.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it does\NTha t was the name of my ha t shop
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.11,0:58:57.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.74,0:58:59.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait here
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.98,0:59:07.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A chair!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.45,0:59:09.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It' s mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.93,0:59:22.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl, get back here
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.14,0:59:32.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, this way please
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.17,1:00:35.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I understand you' re Howl' s mother
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.21,1:00:38.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes\NMy name is Pendragon
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.88,1:00:41.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m sure you re weary\NPlease have a sea t
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.78,1:00:42.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.79,1:00:56.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am Madam Suliman, His Majesty s witch
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.40,1:01:03.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, tha t dog is...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.50,1:01:05.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you mean Heen?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.07,1:01:09.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He does my errands\NI asked him to escort you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.88,1:01:16.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl won' t join us, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.75,1:01:20.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You see, he sends his mother\nto make excuses
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.82,1:01:23.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m sure he' d be utterly useless\nto His Majesty
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.89,1:01:27.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a shame
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.56,1:01:30.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was my last apprentice...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.70,1:01:34.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A student of such marvelous gif ts
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.10,1:01:39.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I rejoiced in finally finding\na worthy heir
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.27,1:01:44.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But then, a demon stole his heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.71,1:01:46.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and he abandoned me
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.98,1:01:51.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He turned his magic\nto purely selfish uses
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.45,1:01:54.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Pendragon
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.19,1:01:57.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That boy is dangerous
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.26,1:02:01.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His power is too grea t\nf or one with no heart
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.59,1:02:06.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If he f ollows tha t path he II wind up\nlike the Witch of the Waste
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.97,1:02:07.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bring her
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.27,1:02:15.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.01,1:02:21.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I just restored her to her real age
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.11,1:02:22.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All her powers are gone
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.31,1:02:27.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once upon a time,\nshe was a magnificent witch
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.85,1:02:30.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She made a bargain with a demon
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.66,1:02:33.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,who consumed her, body and soul,\nlong, long ago
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.36,1:02:37.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our kingdom can no longer a f ford\nto turn a blind eye
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.03,1:02:40.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,to disreputable wizards and witches
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.20,1:02:43.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If Howl comes here\nto serve the kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.70,1:02:46.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I will teach him how to break\nwith the demon
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.01,1:02:50.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If not, I' II strip him of his powers\nas I have taken hers
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.04,1:02:53.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now just a minute
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.68,1:02:57.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand why Howl\nrefused to come here
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.25,1:02:59.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something s not right
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.82,1:03:04.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Forcing your aged guests to climb\nstairs, dragging them into strange rooms
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.26,1:03:05.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s like a trap
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.96,1:03:07.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You call Howl heartless!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.03,1:03:12.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he' s selfish and cowardly\nand unpredictable
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.46,1:03:15.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But he' s straight as an arrow\NHe only wants to be free
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.10,1:03:18.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl won t turn into an evil monster
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.94,1:03:21.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He II ba ttle the demon on his own
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.81,1:03:23.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I believe in him
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.21,1:03:26.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Pendragon...\NYou re in love with Howl
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.78,1:03:30.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl...\NHowl' s coming?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.05,1:03:34.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want Howl s heart, I want it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.32,1:03:37.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s enough from you\NHowl s not coming
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.56,1:03:41.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl will most certainly come
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.56,1:03:45.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I' ve found his weakness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.87,1:03:52.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.04,1:03:54.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As you are
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.74,1:03:56.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How are you f eeling?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.37,1:03:57.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you f or asking
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.78,1:04:01.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Meetings bore me\NI flew out for a breather
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.85,1:04:03.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How lovely
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.21,1:04:04.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,These are?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.05,1:04:07.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is Wizard Howl s mother
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.52,1:04:08.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.79,1:04:17.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I apprecia te it, but I don t intend\nto win any war with magic
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.03,1:04:22.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s true tha t Suliman s powers\nshield our palace from bombs
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.63,1:04:25.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But they just fall on neighboring towns
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.30,1:04:27.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s how magic works\NRight, Suliman?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.01,1:04:30.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such eloquence today, Your Majesty
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.41,1:04:31.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Suliman!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.85,1:04:38.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the final ba ttle\NThis time, we II bea t them to a pulp
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.79,1:04:45.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Suliman, you' ve outdone yourself\nwith tha t double. Await good news
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.06,1:04:47.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you kindly
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.09,1:04:49.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have my generals assembled?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.90,1:04:56.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s been awhile, Howl
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.83,1:04:59.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Delighted to see you doing so well
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.10,1:05:01.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I saw right through you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.34,1:05:03.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ve kept my oa th
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.61,1:05:06.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve no wish to fight you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.28,1:05:07.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II take my mother
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.88,1:05:09.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won' t let you go
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.20,1:05:33.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don t look down,\nyou II be dragged down
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.91,1:05:37.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,lt' s time I showed your mother\nwhat you really are
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.06,1:06:33.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl, don t! It s a trap
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.05,1:06:48.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hold tight
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.99,1:06:57.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, sit up front
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.39,1:07:03.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, Sophie,\nyou brought the whole gang along
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.66,1:07:05.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nice doggie
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.56,1:07:09.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' re just Suliman' s spy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.80,1:07:12.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, too la te to toss you now
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.60,1:07:14.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, you steer
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.24,1:07:16.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What! I can t possibly!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.77,1:07:18.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They' re a f ter us
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.31,1:07:26.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' II tackle them. Fly straight\nto the castle in the Wastes
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.72,1:07:28.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t! That s impossible!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.65,1:07:31.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t worry, the ring will guide you
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.86,1:07:34.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Summon Calcifer with your heart
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.23,1:07:35.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Summon Calcif er?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.13,1:07:40.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It' s glowing
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.63,1:07:44.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Follow the light\NYou' II be there by nightfall
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.74,1:07:48.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why send me to Suliman\nif you were coming yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.34,1:07:50.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your presence gave me\nthe courage f or it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.91,1:07:53.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She s too terrible to\nface on my own
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.95,1:07:57.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You ve saved me\NI was in grave danger back there
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.95,1:08:01.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t let go!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.09,1:08:09.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,- You' re good\N- Stop joking!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.26,1:08:13.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We ve got a lead now
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.33,1:08:17.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can give you 5 minutes of invisibility,\nnow s your chance
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.71,1:08:22.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.39,1:08:36.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.65,1:08:40.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Tha t' s the most fun\NI' ve had in ages
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.59,1:08:43.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I supposed Howl thinks\nhe' s escaped...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.96,1:08:46.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His mother' s awfully young
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.52,1:09:39.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We' re not far\NThat' s my hometown
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.49,1:09:46.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t look so friendly\NI don t trust you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.68,1:10:12.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The castle\NThey' ve come to meet us
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.39,1:10:19.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.99,1:10:21.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Markl, help!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.76,1:10:23.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don' t know how to stop this thing!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.07,1:10:37.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.41,1:10:39.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Doggie
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.95,1:10:42.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Markl
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.92,1:10:45.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m home
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.48,1:10:47.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.62,1:10:49.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' re home!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.69,1:10:52.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming to meet us
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.19,1:11:25.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, you' ve gone too f ar
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.48,1:11:46.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Howl' s back
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.00,1:12:42.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.70,1:13:46.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl? Is it you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.83,1:13:51.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt? In pain?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.84,1:13:54.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.97,1:13:57.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to help you
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.11,1:13:59.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to break the spell you' re under
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.28,1:14:03.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can' t even break your own spell
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.95,1:14:06.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I love you!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.42,1:14:08.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Too la te
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.42,1:14:13.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.90,1:14:28.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl must be back
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.64,1:14:33.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, you' d better figure out\nhow to break my spell quick
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.61,1:14:35.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We re both running out of time
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.95,1:14:38.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning Howl will turn into\na monster? Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.78,1:14:42.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can' t tell you that\NI' m a demon
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.19,1:14:46.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er, Suliman told me,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.59,1:14:49.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl has given you\nsomething very precious
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.69,1:14:51.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t is it?\NWhere is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.70,1:14:54.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s confidential inf ormation
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.63,1:14:57.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And if I threa ten\nto dump wa ter over you?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.27,1:15:00.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you!\NHowl will die with me
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.89,1:15:21.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Turnip
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.53,1:15:23.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We' ve got to be brave
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.76,1:15:28.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ready, Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.07,1:15:32.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,OK! Open wider, Calcifer
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.44,1:15:36.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! Push!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.74,1:15:38.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Heave!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.25,1:15:50.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... said... move!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.16,1:15:52.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.35,1:16:18.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They call it a castle, but once\nyou get inside, it s a junk heap
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.55,1:16:22.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It' s time to ea t!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.19,1:16:30.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here, old girl
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.66,1:16:34.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But, Sophie\nshe' s the Witch of the Waste
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.03,1:16:36.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No need to worry
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.63,1:16:38.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why' s she staring at me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.00,1:16:41.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such a pretty fire
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.24,1:16:45.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.31,1:16:46.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.54,1:16:47.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.65,1:16:49.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Master Howl,\ncan we keep this puppy?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.41,1:16:53.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An old Witch and\NMadam Suliman' s dog
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.48,1:16:55.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why' d you let them in, Calcif er?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.35,1:17:00.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t look a t me!\NThey blew in with Sophie
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.96,1:17:04.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, always dramatic...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.20,1:17:07.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So you' re Turnip
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.03,1:17:12.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You re under quite a spell, too
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.07,1:17:15.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Seems everyone in our little f amily\nis complica ted...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.47,1:17:17.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He' s so handsome
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.31,1:17:21.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a busy day\NWe' re moving
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.61,1:17:22.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Moving?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.65,1:17:25.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good. There aren' t any shops,\nhere in the middle of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.35,1:17:29.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam Suliman can track us down\nin no time, here
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.99,1:17:34.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you' II have to stay behind\NThe magic in your spell' s too risky
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.20,1:17:41.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, that s done
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.37,1:17:44.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take it away, Calcifer
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.55,1:18:01.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.35,1:18:02.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stay right where you are
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.36,1:18:08.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Be gentle...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.80,1:18:12.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.41,1:19:00.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We ve moved\NYou can get up now
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.45,1:19:04.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing, Master\nlt' s so grand
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.28,1:19:07.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t a pretty fire
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.97,1:19:23.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.57,1:19:27.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I added a bathroom\NFor our growing f amily
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.37,1:19:30.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, come here!\NSophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.68,1:19:36.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I added a bedroom, too\NGo in
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.22,1:19:48.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is... why?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.23,1:19:52.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would suit you\NDo you like it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.83,1:19:57.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it' s perfect\nf or a housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.30,1:20:00.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I got you new clothes, too\NOpen them later. Next
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.14,1:20:03.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie! Come here!\NQuick!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.71,1:20:06.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A courtyard!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.28,1:20:07.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There s a shop, too
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.45,1:20:10.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let s go, Heen!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.78,1:20:13.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See that new color on the dial?\NThere s a new exit
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.29,1:20:20.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My gif t to you, Sophie\NStep outside
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.42,1:20:47.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s my secret garden
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.02,1:20:49.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.89,1:20:54.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make it with your magic?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.53,1:20:57.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Only a little, to help the flowers
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.50,1:21:09.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Howl!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.14,1:21:10.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lt' s like I' m dreaming
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.63,1:21:34.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.23,1:21:40.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How mysterious\NI f eel I' ve been here before
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.90,1:21:42.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I could cry with happiness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.14,1:21:44.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.62,1:21:53.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.22,1:22:00.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A sweet little house
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.82,1:22:02.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My f avorite hideaway
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.36,1:22:07.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I was little I spent\nmy summers there alone
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.60,1:22:10.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Alone?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.57,1:22:14.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My Uncle, the Wizard,\nlef t it to me in secret
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.67,1:22:17.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourself a t home there, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.01,1:22:22.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.71,1:22:23.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m scared
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.88,1:22:26.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m afraid you' II go of f and disappear\nsomewhere, once I m inside
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.65,1:22:31.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl, tell me the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.99,1:22:34.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don' t mind if you re a monster
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.53,1:22:44.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make sure tha t\nyou' II all live comfortably
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.47,1:22:48.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why not a flower shop,\nwith all these flowers?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.94,1:22:51.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' d be good a t it, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.54,1:22:53.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then, you' d go away?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.48,1:22:58.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to help you, Howl
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.85,1:23:02.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m not beautiful\nand I' m only good a t cleaning...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.09,1:23:05.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, you are beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.79,1:23:13.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The good thing about being old\nis tha t you' ve so little to lose...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.11,1:23:28.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why' s that flying here?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.08,1:23:29.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A battleship?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.05,1:23:31.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,On its way to burn cities and people
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.05,1:23:33.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy' s? Ours?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.35,1:23:35.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What diff erence does it make?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.90,1:23:49.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Murderers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.64,1:23:59.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look at all those bombs
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.49,1:24:16.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It stopped
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.83,1:24:18.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.53,1:24:21.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m just tinkering\NIt won t crash
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.63,1:24:25.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.70,1:24:28.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, looks like they re onto us
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.91,1:24:41.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam Suliman' s deputies\NLet' s go back
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.12,1:24:43.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Run! Move those legs
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.53,1:24:58.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry on in!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.87,1:25:00.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don' t let go!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.18,1:25:11.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t happened, Sophie?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.05,1:25:14.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ve had it with this place!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.63,1:25:26.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.60,1:25:27.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good night
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.80,1:25:34.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t worry about Master Howl, Sophie\NSometimes, he' s gone for days on end
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.31,1:25:36.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Markl
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.21,1:25:38.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Need the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.31,1:25:39.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m fine
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.78,1:25:41.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good night
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.05,1:25:43.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' re in love
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.95,1:25:49.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sighing away like that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.00,1:26:02.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.97,1:26:05.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Were you ever in love?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.40,1:26:08.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I was\NI' m still in love
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.44,1:26:09.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha t?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.87,1:26:13.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Men, why ever should we want them...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.24,1:26:15.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But a young man s heart is so delicious!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.01,1:26:17.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.95,1:26:20.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And so adorable, too
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.89,1:26:25.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is tha t?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.49,1:26:26.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Air raid siren
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.82,1:26:28.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Air raid?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.13,1:26:34.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It s not for here\NBut best not go out tonight
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.73,1:26:40.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Suliman' s creatures are searching\nhigh and low f or our house
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.24,1:26:47.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a good fire,\nhiding us so well
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.65,1:27:25.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, a stranger got in!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.62,1:27:33.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.92,1:27:36.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.30,1:27:41.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you been!\NI searched for you everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.70,1:27:44.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But, oh, look how you' ve aged!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.87,1:27:46.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lt' s all my f ault
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.77,1:27:51.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m so sorry, Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.01,1:27:53.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.91,1:27:58.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I barely recognize the house
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.38,1:28:00.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.25,1:28:02.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, your landlady
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.42,1:28:05.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sophie, I' ve got a new husband!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.96,1:28:08.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He' s such a wonderful man\NAnd he' s rich, too!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.83,1:28:10.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can all live together again
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.73,1:28:13.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You' II never have to clean again
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.80,1:28:16.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I m happy here...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.03,1:28:18.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.67,1:28:19.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, I f orgot
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.90,1:28:22.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My car' s waiting\NI ve got to run
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.84,1:28:30.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I m so glad I f ound you again
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.48,1:28:32.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We' II really catch up next time
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.65,1:28:34.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the meantime, you take care
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.52,1:28:44.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A peeping-bug, eh?\NThe oldest trick in the book, Suliman
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.73,1:28:46.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All yours, Cal
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.84,1:28:58.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,May you find happiness, Mother
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.31,1:29:00.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you\NYou too, Sophie
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.95,1:29:08.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve done wha t I was told\NTake me back to my husband
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.28,1:29:11.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I m sure Madam Suliman\nwill be pleased
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.39,1:29:15.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Sophie...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.23,1:29:20.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look a t all these people
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.33,1:29:24.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They' re all running away\NThe town will be empty
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.73,1:29:27.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you wish to run, too?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.04,1:29:30.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That' s what tha t lady spoke of...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.61,1:29:33.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, she did\NI m glad we made up
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.24,1:29:36.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t go, Sophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.18,1:29:40.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I love you, Sophie\NPlease stay
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.92,1:29:44.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I love you, too, Markl\NDon t worry, I won' t go
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.89,1:29:46.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.16,1:29:48.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are we a family?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.86,1:29:50.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we' re family
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.19,1:29:52.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.90,1:30:03.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I II never let Suliman\nget hold of Howl
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.52,1:30:22.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But the paper says we won
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.79,1:30:25.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Only fools swallow such lies
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.70,1:30:30.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How strange\NI can t get Calcif er going
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.90,1:30:32.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma, will you stop tha t?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.94,1:30:34.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such an awful stink
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.60,1:30:37.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why deny an old lady her pleasures
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.24,1:30:40.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Open the window, Markl
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.95,1:30:46.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn t open tha t now...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.92,1:30:52.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In Calcif er s present sta te,\nhe can t possibly keep them out
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.56,1:30:55.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Markl!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.44,1:31:07.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Close it quick!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.31,1:31:16.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look a f ter Grandma, Markl\NI' II check on the shop
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.80,1:31:39.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you, now? If you ve\nenergy to spare, put out the fires
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.29,1:32:05.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.88,1:32:20.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dramatic as usual...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.69,1:32:34.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.73,1:32:39.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m sorry\NI had too many enemies, tonight
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.96,1:32:42.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl, oh, Howl
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.62,1:33:01.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Master Howl!\NSophie!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.45,1:33:07.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calcif er, be strong
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.26,1:33:16.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, was that a gift\nfrom Suliman?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.87,1:33:19.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That granny f ed me something nasty
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.50,1:33:22.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, if it isn' t Howl
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.47,1:33:27.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I feel we need a nice long cha t
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.74,1:33:31.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise, Madam\NBut we ve no time, now
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.12,1:33:36.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How unlike you\NYou' re not running away
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.42,1:33:38.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Until later, then
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.99,1:33:42.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stay here, Sophie\NCalcif er will protect you
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.19,1:33:44.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I II see to things outside
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.70,1:33:47.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Howl!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.16,1:33:49.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don' t go! Please stay
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.27,1:33:53.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Another round of bombs is coming\NEven Calcifer can' t stop those
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.10,1:33:56.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let' s run away\NDon' t fight
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.44,1:33:59.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' m through running away
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.64,1:34:02.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I' ve finally f ound someone\NI want to protect...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.88,1:34:04.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.82,1:34:09.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Howl!
